calculate_TTR <- function(x){
  require(quanteda)
  ntype(x)/lengths(x)
}

From scratch

calculate_ttr_threshold <- function(this_snippet, TTR_limit = 0.72, base_snippet_length = 20) {
  # @param this_snippet must be a list of strings 
  # TTR_limit Type Token Ratio
  # base_snippet_length num words to start calculating TTR with, default = 20
  current_TTR <- 1
  snip_of_snippet_length <- base_snippet_length
  
  while (current_TTR >= TTR_limit) {
    current_snip_of_snippet <- this_snippet[1:snip_of_snippet_length]
    numtypes <- length(unique(tokens(current_snip_of_snippet)))
    numtokens <- length(current_snip_of_snippet)
    
    current_TTR <- numtypes / numtokens # recalculate TTR
    snip_of_snippet_length <- snip_of_snippet_length + 1 # increment snippet_length
  }
  return(snip_of_snippet_length)
}

calculate_mtld <- function(text, TTR = 0.72, num_snippets = 25) {
  # @param text : as character
  # @param TTR : TTR threshold
  # @param num_snippets : num places to take TTR measurement
  require(quanteda)
  tokenized_text <- as.character(unlist(tokens_tolower(tokens(text, remove_punct = TRUE)))) # preprocessing opts
  num_words <- length(tokenized_text)
  snippet_size <- floor(num_words / num_snippets)

  mtld_lengths <- vector()
  
  for (i in 1:num_snippets) {
    this_snippet <- tokenized_text[(i + snippet_size * (i-1)) :(snippet_size * i) ]
    
    mtld_lengths <- c(mtld_lengths, calculate_ttr_threshold(this_snippet, TTR = TTR) )
  }
  
  return(mean(mtld_lengths))
}

# Run it
calculate_mtld(fdr_1936)
## [1] 63.48
calculate_mtld(fdr_1945)
## [1] 83.52

5c Creating blocks

# Function to extract a block from a text
# @param words : Text in array-of-words form
# @param index : block number
# @param block_length : num words in block
extract_block <- function(words, index, block_length) {
  start <- (index - 1) * block_length + 1
  end <- index * block_length
  paste(words[start:end], collapse = " ")
}

# Function to convert a array of words into a list of blocks of words. 
# @param text: (array of words)
# @param block_length: num of words in block
text_to_blocks <- function(words, block_length) {
  
  numblocks <- floor(length(words)/block_length) # calculate number of blocks for the book, rounding down -- will drop the last partial block
  lapply(1:numblocks, function(i) { extract_block(words, i, block_length) # lapply the extract_block function for each block from 1 to the last complete block
  })
}
## Running it

# Make an array, each element of which is another array of all words (in order) from one book
texts_words <- lapply(texts, function(text) {
  strsplit(text, " ")[[1]]
})

# Make the blocks of text from all books (each element of texts_words)
texts_blocks <- lapply(texts_words, function(words) {
  text_to_blocks(words, 1700)
})

# Last step: flatten list of lists of blocks into one list of all blocks
alltextsblocks <- unlist(texts_blocks)

## Making docnames for all blocks

# make a list (of same length as alltextsblocks) containing name of book and block #

  filename <- filenames[index]

    paste(filename, "block", block_index, sep = " ")
  }))
}))

Question 7

# Heap's Law

#      M = kT^b

# M = vocab size
# T = number of tokens
# k, b are constants

num_tokens <- sum(rowSums(austen_dickens_dfm))

M <- nfeat(austen_dickens_dfm)

k <- 44

b <- log(M/k)/log(num_tokens)
b
## [1] 0.4562574

clusterExport(cl, "lab_sent")

# Bootstrap function
system.time(results <- foreach(i = 1:75, .combine = rbind) %dopar% {
  samp <- corpus_sample(lab_sent, 2000)
  FRE <- textstat_readability(samp, measure = "Flesch")
  data.frame(Year = docvars(samp)[,"Year"],
             Flesch = FRE,
             Sim = i) %>%
    group_by(Year) %>% 
    summarise(FRE = mean(Flesch.Flesch), 
              Sim = mean(Sim))
})
##    user  system elapsed 
##   0.170   0.016  21.900
# Frees up your computer's processor cores for other uses
stopCluster(cl)

# Standard error function
std <- function(x) sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))

# Calculating the mean and standard error of the FRE
results_summed <- results %>% 
  group_by(Year) %>% 
  summarise(FRE_mean = mean(FRE), # Calculates the average FRE score
            FRE_sd = std(FRE)) # Calculates Standard Error for the FRE score
             
results_summed <- results_summed %>% 
  mutate(
    FRE_025 = FRE_mean - 2 * FRE_sd, # Creates the low end of the 95% confidence interval
    FRE_975 = FRE_mean + 2*FRE_sd # Creates the high end of the 95% confidence interval
  )

# Estimating the FRE directly from the text
direct_results <- data.frame(
  FRE = textstat_readability(labour_manifestos, measure = "Flesch"),
  Year = docvars(labour_manifestos)[,"Year"]
) %>% group_by(Year)

# Graph estimated and base FRE scores by President with CI
results_summed$FRE_direct <- direct_results$FRE.Flesch

limits <- aes(ymax = results_summed$FRE_975, ymin=results_summed$FRE_025)

ggplot(aes(x = Year), data = results_summed) +
  geom_point(aes(y = FRE_mean), size = 2, color = "blue") +
  geom_errorbar(limits, width=.5) + 
  geom_point(aes(y = FRE_direct), size = 1, color = "red") + 
  coord_flip() + 
  theme_bw() +
  ylab("FRE Mean") + 
  xlab("Year")

dev.off()
